By Rachel Tackett

About 12 kilometers off the coast of Ozu City in Ehime Prefecture, there lies a tiny landmass, less than a kilometer wide, which is completely overrun by cats. This little island is home to only 15 human residents, all of retirement age, but houses more than 100 kitties.
